        <div class="w3-container w3-light-blue w3-margin-bottom">
            <h2>Start your morning breakfast with Idli & Dosa</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="w3-twothird w3-margin-bottom">
            <img src="images/Idli_Dosa_breakfast.jpg" style="width: 90% " height="600">
        </div>
        <div class="w3-third w3-margin-bottom">
            <p>
                Idlis and dosas are probably the most popular breakfast foods in India. Though they originated in South India, idlis and dosas have gained nation-wide recognition now.
                <br />
                <br />
                Steamed, puffy and delectable, Idli doused in the ever-so soothing sambhar sure makes for one of the nation's most favourite breakfast.It is not oily or greasy, yet it is considered to be one of the most delicious regional snacks. It is a popular street food, yet shares no infamous reputation of being unhealthy or calorie-laden.
                <br />
                <br />
                Dosas are not just a treat for your taste buds, but also light on your digestive system. Prepared from rice and lentils, dosa is fermented breakfast option, which makes it easy for your body to assimilate and digest it.Dosa is also a great source of healthy carbohydrates. Dosa and sambhar both are made from lentils, which provide a good amount of protein to your body.

            </p>
        </div>

