            <p>
                Caution: The samosas are not healthy at all,the only benefit it provides is the emotional connect to Indians as they may get a quick nostalgia of their street food outings.

                The good thing is that most Indians do not eat samosas every day either but the Chai is still a must in lot of house-holds So here are the benefits of chai

                <br />1. Protect against free-radicals: For one thing, chai’s black-tea base is rich in powerful antioxidants that protect cells from free-radical damage.

                <br />2. Improves digestion: Black teas have also been found to positively impact gut bacteria, boosting strains that help improve metabolism and prevent bloating.

                <br />3. Helps keeps hormones balanced: Research has found that drinking black tea may even change the way women’s genes are expressed, helping balance hormones, reduce inflammation, and possibly prevent cancer.

                <br />4. Strengthens immune system: Consider the fact that chai is also blended with an array of antioxidant-rich spices, each one with some pretty powerful, science-backed healing traits of its own. Ginger, for one, is known to have anti-nausea properties, while also helping to reduce inflammation and strengthen the immune system. Cardamom and black pepper also have digestive superpowers, further boosting chai’s reputation as a potent stomach savior.
            </p>
        </div>

