              "Roti is a whole wheat version of naan bread," says Lauren Minchen, MPH, RDN, CDN. It can be made from a variety of unrefined grains including millet, jowar, bajra, and whole wheat.
              <br />
              <br />It's always best not to overdo it on the bread basket, given how carb-heavy most Indian dishes can be. But if you can't knock the craving, opt for roti since it's easier to digest and more nutritious because of its healthier grain base.
            </p>
